  "text": "Injury Incidence Calculation and Statistical Analysis: Calculating incidence: 1) injury per activity (total number of injuries/number of activities), 2) injury per 1000 hours (1000 × total number of injuries / total activity hours), and 3) total activity hours (for match: 11 players × 1.5 hours; for training: number of players participating in the training × 1.5 hours). [CITATION_1] Crosstabulation, frequency analysis (frequencies) and descriptive statistics methods were used in the statistical analysis. The difference between match and training injuries was calculated with chi-square test as the sufficient data were obtained. All of the statistics were evaluated by SPSS 10.0 for Windows (SPSS Inc, Chicago, IL).",
